Tatoos and piercings in excess are gross, I don't really care what anyone says.

I would delete that tripe, but I like people to peruse my journal and take notice to what sick people waste time online.

Oh, and tell your dad I said thanks, braaahman.

I made the mistake of sleeping ALL DAY yesterday. I think there's something wrong with me. I couldn't get up. I just layed there. I didn't even go out. So here it is 5AM and I'm wide awake. 

I made friends with this girl recently - her name is Katie. Her parents own this bar in Lawerenceville called 'Ray's.' It's really cool - kinda dingy, but decorated with lots of vintage shit. Totally hip. She is too. It's sort of a blessing and a curse becoming friends with someone so fast. I try not to let my gaurd down, and emotions fly out, but when you meet someone...sometimes you just...'know.' You get this feeling that's like no other feeling. When you meet someone you immediately connect with, who understands and feels everything you say, who shares some of the same pleasures, the same vices, the same bad habits. Someone you can laugh with, and cry with. She's moving back to Florida (she was home for the summer), for school this weekend, and today is the last time I'm going to see her for a really long time. I'm so upset, and have this terrible feeling of anxiety right now. I barely talk to any of my friends anymore. When I meet new people, sometimes I feel like I'm filling the void of my friends with random people. I'm trying to make them fit this mold...I mold them into what I want them to be to me instead of what they really are. It wasn't like that with Katie. 

Things are so different now, and I'm slowly starting to realize how much growing up sucks.

Dip it low, pick it up slow
Roll it all around, poke it out, let your back roll
Pop, pop, pop that thang
I'mma show you how to make your man say, "Oh"

Am I the only one who loves this song?

It makes my wiener hard.

'I crawl into my cave with bloodshot eyes Little sugar pills to ease my mind.' This most describes my summer thus far. Jimbo's 3 top summer moments : 3. Being invited to the Z100 party, and pissing my pants before I got to the door in front of 1/2 of Pittsburgh's most famous people (what the fuck do Edgar Snyder and Sally Wiggin give a fuck anyway?) 2. Side swiping some ladies car while trying to parallel park in Shadyside, and not-so-non chalantly pulling two spaces down instead...in front of an entire crowd at an outside bar. Random : "Do you know how to drive?" Jimbo : "I'm from Greensburg. We don't have to know how to parallel park." 1. Meeting Juliana Hatfield. Things to look forward to : 3. Hopefully a trip to Chicago to visit some hot sluts I know. 2. Finishing this shitty thing called school. 1. Being cooler then everyone I know. Peace.

I had a wild assed weekend. Wild assed week infact! I promised myself I would slow down on drinking, but I haven't gotten wild in awhile. On Wednesday I went to a St. Pat's party, and some cover band was playing - the singer of the band sits in front of me in phiolosophy and randomly turns around and sings Liz Phair songs to me. They were playing 'Top 40' radio hits, everyone in the bar was WASTED - I have never seen this place so packed, it's a sports bar mind you. There had to have been a good 250 people in this place. After a punk version of Toxic (haha), I start to hear 'Get a load of me, get a load of you...' I thought I was trippin. Then they played Extraordinary with guest vocals from yours truly. The explanation was, 'I would sing this, but my friend Jimmy knows all the words, and his voice is nasaly and monotone like Liz's.' Is this a compliment? Anyway, I sang and I rocked. I even plucked a chord or two (I just wanted to hold a guitar and pretend to be cool). I'm not really shy, but I'm not that outgoing either. I had people from school saying hi to me the following day I've never seen before. They must have been mesmerized (or frightened) by my performance. It's so wierd having 250 or so people staring at you, but cool to have them sing along. I want to be in a band, but write my own songs. I could definitely see where the stage fright comes in. I've been shitting and spitting green beer all week. Not pretty. Thursday...drank at happy hour, and drank again later after my plans failed. Was wasted! Friday...My friends Gavin and Raime were home. We went to BWW for the Pitt game and then to dance. I usually never buy shots, but I was all over it. And all under a table! Saturday...My friend Amber came home and we went with Raime and Gavin to BWW (we live in that place), and to get our grooves on at this new club. It's like a ghetto version of a club in Pittsburgh. They charge you $1 to get in, when we should actually be paying them. I was so wasted that I said something along the lines of some lady looking like she raided Madonna's yard sale. Spandex skirts and leather jackets never looked so trashy. Without further ado, I finally got some piccas developed. They're from sometime earlier this year. I didn't get any of Amber, which sucks because I wanted to see the difference in her boobs. And yes, she DID get a boob job, BITCHES, and don't fucking hate. Anyway... This is Gavin, he's Raime's boyfriend. He lives in Rochester. A cool cat! This is my friend Jen when I went to OU in Athens for New Years. Chug a lug! Jen before the Liz Phair show. This is me being a tard. Such a bad angle, my nose looks even more frightening than usual. Raime and Gavin. Don't you hate seing people in love? My friend Katie on New Years - this is right before she dropped the champagne bottle on the floor and it was in my shoes for a week. Jen on New Year's again Consequently, this was Jen that night That's all for now. Jimbo
Damn right! 'Scuse me while I go clean up my sticky drawers!

I can't even begin to describe this weekend. It wasn't your usual Jimmy fashioned I drank, got wasted, affair. It was a fucking nightmare! I had to get my teeth pulled. The actual pulling didn't hurt, it was when my dentist was twisting my neck like it was a beer bottle, and that disgusting cracking sound as my tooth was being pulled. Since the teeth that were pulled were right next to each other, it hurts even more. I can't believe I let my teeth get this way. I was the first of my friends with retainers, and then braces; I think I built up this fear and immunity towards the dentist. Now I'm paying for it in a big way. Thank God the teeth that were pulled were on the side where no one can see them, or else I'd look like a jack-o-lantern. I was put on Vicoden, and whoever said they're addictive was damn right. Even when I feel I have a minor ache or pain, I take one. I swear they make me hallucinate - I've been having the ODDEST dreams lately, and waking up in pools of sweat with a fallen asleep arm. My mouth isn't in pain anymore, but I have the grossest taste in my mouth from this tooth. I haven't smoked in 3 days, I could probably quit if I wanted to. Dry sockets are all I need. Two of my friends came to visit me on Saturday; they brought me popsickles and we watched a movie. Given the number of friends I have and the fact that only two of them stop to think about me is baffling. I have friends driving 4 hours out of there way to visit me, and friends that live 5 minutes away that can't even call me, or stop over to say 'hi.' It really pisses me off and disappoints me. I'm always complaining about something, but this is why. People prove my point that they're not good friends. Everyfuckingtime. But when they need something, who's first on the call list? You guessed it! I don't ask for much, but a little respect and recognition now and then would be cool. I have 2 jobs, yet it seems like I have none since I get no hours. What is a person supposed to do for money around here? Someone asked me to apply at CD Warehouse for the summer. I might do it. One of the questions on the application asks 'what radio station' I listen to. I'm thinking of a smart assed answer about how radio ruins the world, hope they look past that. These pills also give me severe mood swings; more so then usual. I have the sudden urge to go and break my cats neck. Peace.

presents LIZ PHAIR SOLD OUT w/ Wheat - Rachel Yamagata Saturday, March 27 If anyone would like to make up for it by playing gee-tar, wearing no clothes, and singing to me about getting fucked backwards so's they can watch TV, gimme a ring a ding ding. I'm thinking of going to Baltimore to see Sleater-Kinney at the end of April. But I'm assuming they'll be playing new, yet to be recorded stuff that I can't sing obnoxiously along too. We'll see. I'm going to breakfast with my buds that slept over. Lata. Jimbo

I just made the most amazing Juliana 2 CD Set. It's fucking epic, and amazing. Arranged by James E. Stevenson! It includes her solo work, as well as a few Some Girls songs, and her time spent with her old band, The Blake Babies from '01, a couple unreleased tracks, a couple of demos. This is a perfect Juliana starter kit. I made it mainly for Lauren, and my car, and yes, I have no life! I had to pass some time - I'm getting like 90 of my teeth pulled tomorow. Here is the tracklisting: Disk I 1. Hotels 2. Table For One 3. Bad Day 4. Fleur de Lys 5. Choose Drugs 6. Live On Tomorow 7. Feel It 8. Swan Song 9. Nothing Ever Happens 10. OK OK 11. My Sister 12. Almost True 13. Close Your Eyes 14. For The Birds 15. Disappear 16. Better Than Nothing 17. Dying Proof 18. Until Tomorow 19. Little Pieces 20. Malted Milk Disk II 1. Daniel 2. You Blues 3. Spin The Bottle 4. Baby Gets High 5. Don't Rush Me 6. Running Out 7. I Got No Idols 8. Somebody's Waiting For Me 9. Cry In The Dark 10. Mountains of Love 11. Sneaking Around 12. Cybil 13. Dumb Fun 14. Slow Motion 15. What A Life 16. Neccessito 17. Bottles & Flowers 18. Supermodel 19. Cool Rock Boy 20. Robot City 21. Universal Heart-Beat I tried to make it an even, and fair mix and sample of each of her albums and then some. Juliana Hatfield is one of those artists who can't be contained to a simple 2-cd set, but putting just 21 songs on 1 cd was even more impossible. I'm passing these samples out to the music staff at school as well - all of whom are interested in her. I love spreading love, and superb taste. Also - in case anyone is interested in hearing Kristin Hersh's new band, here's some MP3's from a radio show they just did for KEXP in Seattle. 50 FT Wave is definitely different from Throwing Muses. Very loud, very balls to the walls, very fast, punkish. The link : http://cassettefetish.com/50footwave/ G'Night! Jimbo

Oh baby, know what you're like? You're like my favorite underwear It just feels right you know it. Liz, you hot slut! ROCK ME AND ROLL ME HOLD ME TIGHT TEAR ME APART AND MAKE ME NEW, LIKE YOU ALWAYS DO! Anyway! I worked out today. I'm so buff. So many haters were staring at me and Max because we were eating doritos at treadmill(s) numero 5/6. Fuck you! If you had my thigh muscles, you'd be eating doritos too! I also cleaned my room today. My walls are looking hot - totally maxed out with pictures/bulletin board(s), memorabilia I splurged off ebay over the past few years. I have a camera full of pictures I need to get developed. I took a picture of my wall. I'll try to post them soon. I'm kind of scared to see the photos - they date back from summer and span the whole year. I was so out of control with drinking this summer. I'm so glad I sobered up some without the help of AA. Everytime I eat lunch at school, there's an AA meeting going on at the cafeteria next to me. I'm SO tempted to take over a bottle of wine and just accidentily drop it on the floor. It's supposed to be so nice out this week - I want to do something fun. Maybe I'll strap on my fishing coat and catch some dolphins? Ideas? Send them! Jimbo

I'm SO excited about Juliana Hatfield's new record. Here's some of the new press photos : Perfectly hot. It's called 'In Exile Deo' (cool, huh?) and hits shelves on May 18th. She's announcing some tour dates soon. Her shows are intense, and emotionally draining. I can't wait. This weekend was mad craziness. Raime and I ventured to Clarion for Amber's sorority's date party. What could have been lame ended out fun as fuck, made 10,000 times better by Amber's dramatics and throwing cheese and lemons at some douchebag. We were almost kicked out, but in the end, evil prevailed. We were bagged out by some girl in Amber's sorority. How sisterly, you know? And then I was corrected (online mind you) by that same do - gooder today. Get the fuck out of my business, bitch. I worked at AE today. It's SO boring, and people can be such volatile, irritating bitches. This Brian kid I work with totally COMPETES with me to try and sell more, and it's fucking annoying. He'll see me waiting on someone and he'll purposely steal them, give them a fitting room, and send them to the cash register with his name on their brain. I have to try extra hard to be 1/2 as nice as everyone else, so give me a fucking break. I'm getting better on the cash register. I swear. It sounds like it's not a rough job, but it is. It's so irritating having to fold, and refold clothes because people's crusty paws just throw the shit wherever, and it's the only store in the mall with NO air conditioning. So of course I have to go to work 1/2 naked, and have my co-workers stare at me, few of which are female. That's all I have to bitch about for right now. G'Night.

Apparantly, I'll suck even after I'm dead, and people still conive off of me...

I love Ms. Phair, but her photo shoots are getting racier and racier. Is this HONESTLY what it takes to sell records? It's one thing to make a 'different' record, it's another to compromise your integrity. I recall Liz saying she wouldn't pose for Playboy, because it's not the 'proper forum' to display her goodies. But apparantly Maxim is? Maxim is for old, gross, smelly crotched guys with nothing to do on a Saturday night except jack off until their dicks are chafed. Some find these photos arousing, others find them perplexing. I gave you PHAIR warning. ;) Maxim : Paris Hilton and Nicole Ritchie wish they were as cool as Liz! In concert (arm socks!): My 'special' ;) and dear friend Lauren wrote the greatest, most thought provoking essay about Liz and her recent turn. I never thought of it this way, and I respect her point of view. So I'm copying her debate. Sorry Lauren. --------------------------- [ The thing about Liz that upsets me is not really that her album is top 40 friendly rock. Though annoying, it isn't really new among artists I respect. Fucking Nirvana is revolutionary, and yet Teen Spirit is pretty fucking bubble gum for them. It's not even that she wears mini skirts and a headset in her mid-30's. Hello? Madonna? It's that somewhere out there is The Man. We all know The Man. He is everywhere. And right now he is convincing Liz Phair, who ten years ago was able to be Man-friendly in an anti-Man sort of way, that it's a good idea for her to visibly lose all inch of self-respect that she could have had a hit album and kept all the same. Instead of corny, that Maxim photoshoot looked trashy. It could have been ironic fun, and yet it looks depressing and sad. Liz is hot, but those photos are not. The Man is telling Liz Phair that she should tell the media that fuck her fans, she's gonna make some dough. Because it might help people come to terms with her change of sound and fuck the fans that don't get it. They're now bad fans who want to see Liz Phair poor on the streets eating out coochies for a dime. Bad ex-fans! Bad! This strategy didn't work because the only people who would have bought that album anyway felt personally insulted, and the ones they STILL bought that album have hardly kept it on consistent rotation. And the new fans? Well the new ones decided Liz Phair was pretty catchy and bought Exile and are probably still in their closet weeping about the bad girl who said those evil things about wee wees. Because The Man decided that Liz Phair's new audience should be Lincoln Park trixies and girls under 15. That the old audience had gotten, well old, being in their late-twenties and older. And who wants to sell records to those hundreds of millions of buyers with plenty of disposable income? The Man told Liz Phair that it was a good idea to try and be Michelle Branch instead of Liz Phair, who is a goddess and could have pulled off sexy at 36 by looking 36 instead of being 36 and trying to look 22. The Man whispered these things into Liz Phair's ear and sent a buzzing into her brain. Her poignant, poetic songs about divorce and sex and marriage and being single and having a child and thinking he's the most amazing thing in the world, have turned into songs about playing Playstation with the Ashton to her Demi. And it's not a thorough change. I think there are still remnants of the old Liz, and songs on that album that still fit those descriptions, but the change is there. And the worst of it all is that Liz Phair bought it hook, line, and sinker. The Man has won and Liz has lost. ] --------------------------- I do miss the sound of Exile. The way Liz could formulate words and phrases. The way she wrote about things that were never talked about publicly. There's a difference between the innocence, horror, and honesty of 'Fuck and Run' - a situation that happens so much, but is discussed so little, and the jangly upbeat ode to sperm (see 'Hot White Come'). It's very contrived. Forced. Liz will always be known as a potty mouth; she has been from day one. It's like she's still forcing herself to be naughty, yet still retain her mainstream acceptance. Is integrity more important, or being America's hottest rock star M.I.L.F? I'll let you make the call. Personally, I like her old shit, I like her new shit. I don't care what she does, or doesn't wear. Well, maybe just a little. Jimbo
